---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

export const prerender = true;

const lastUpdated = "April 2, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Refund Policy — Visupair"
  description="How refunds and cancellations work for Visupair orders: physical goods, digital products, and services."
>
  <div class="account-page">
    <div class="legal-island">
      <article class="legal-page">
        <header class="legal-header">
          <p class="legal-kicker">Legal</p>
          <h1 class="legal-title">Refund Policy</h1>
          <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="legal-body">
          <p>
            This Refund Policy explains how <strong>Visupair</strong> handles
            refunds and cancellations for orders placed on
            <a href="https://visupair.com">visupair.com</a>. It works together
            with the
            <a href="/legal/terms-of-service">Terms of Service</a>. If
            mandatory consumer laws in your country give you stronger rights,
            those rights still apply.
          </p>

          <h2>1. How to request a refund or cancellation</h2>
          <p>
            Email
            <a href="mailto:info@visupair.com">info@visupair.com</a> from the
            address used for the order (or describe the order number and date).
            Visupair will confirm eligibility and next steps. Approved refunds
            are returned to the original payment method when possible; timing
            depends on banks and the payment provider.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Physical products</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              If an item is <strong>damaged</strong>, <strong>defective</strong>,
              or <strong>not what you ordered</strong>, contact Visupair within
              <strong>14 days</strong> of delivery with a short description and,
              if helpful, photos. Visupair may offer a replacement, repair, or
              refund, including reasonable return shipping where applicable under
              the law.
            </li>
            <li>
              For <strong>change of mind</strong>, EU/EEA/UK consumers often have
              a <strong>14-day right of withdrawal</strong> for distance
              contracts, with exceptions (for example sealed goods opened, or
              custom-made items clearly personalised). Packaged goods must stay
              in condition suitable for resale unless inspection was necessary. If
              the law allows withdrawal, you may need to return the item; direct
              costs of return may apply unless Visupair states otherwise or the
              law requires otherwise.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Handmade or made-to-order</strong> items may be excluded
              from withdrawal once production has clearly started with your
              agreement, or as stated on the product page. Check the listing and
              confirmation email.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. Digital products</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Digital goods (downloads, files, access links) are usually
              delivered instantly or shortly after payment. In many places,
              <strong>the right to withdraw ends once delivery has begun</strong>
              if you explicitly agreed to immediate delivery and acknowledged
              that you may lose the withdrawal right. By completing checkout for
              digital products, you typically confirm that you want immediate
              supply where that applies.
            </li>
            <li>
              If you <strong>cannot access</strong> a purchase due to a technical
              fault on Visupair’s side, email Visupair. Visupair will work to fix
              access or, if that is not possible, may refund or credit at
              Visupair’s reasonable discretion.
            </li>
            <li>
              Refunds for digital products for <strong>change of mind</strong>
              are generally <strong>not</strong> offered once the content has
              been supplied, except where the law requires otherwise.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Services and custom work</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Creative <strong>services</strong> and <strong>custom
              commissions</strong> follow the cancellation rules on the relevant
              service page or written agreement (including any deposit or
              milestone payments).
            </li>
            <li>
              If <strong>you cancel</strong> after Visupair has started work,
              amounts covering work already performed or costs already incurred
              may be retained where permitted by law and as described in the
              offer.
            </li>
            <li>
              If Visupair <strong>cannot deliver</strong> as agreed (for example
              after a reasonable period and communication), Visupair will refund
              amounts paid for undelivered work, unless the Terms or contract
              say otherwise in line with the law.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. Orders cancelled by Visupair</h2>
          <p>
            If Visupair refuses or cancels an order (for example obvious price or
            listing error, legal restriction, or stock issue), Visupair will
            refund any payment taken for that order.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Courses (if applicable)</h2>
          <p>
            If Visupair sells or hosts <strong>courses</strong>, access and refund
            rules for each course appear on that course’s page or at checkout.
            Where no separate rule is stated, the digital-product section above
            applies.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Chargebacks and abuse</h2>
          <p>
            Contacting Visupair first usually resolves issues faster than a bank
            chargeback. Visupair may dispute chargebacks that do not match the
            facts or this Policy. Abuse of refunds or payment systems may lead to
            account restrictions or refusal of future orders.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Refund questions:
            <a href="mailto:info@visupair.com">info@visupair.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .account-page {
    padding: 0 12px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-island {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    min-height: calc(100vh - 420px);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: stretch;
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2.75rem) clamp(1.1rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
  }

  .legal-page {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: min(90ch, 100%);
    margin-inline: auto;
    text-align: start;
    padding-block: 0.25rem 1rem;
    animation: legalFadeIn 0.45s ease-out;
    flex: 1;
  }

  @keyframes legalFadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(6px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    text-align: start;
  }

  .legal-kicker {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .legal-meta {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-body {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.25vw + 0.96rem, 1.0625rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary, var(--foreground));
    text-align: start;
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 2.25rem 0 0.65rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .legal-body p {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1.25rem;
    padding-inline-start: 1.35rem;
    list-style-position: outside;
  }

  .legal-body li {
    margin: 0 0 0.55rem;
    padding-inline-start: 0.2rem;
  }

  .legal-body li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--accent, #a78bfa);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal-body a:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
  }
</style>
